                            <div class="mt-6">
                                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">The Future of Web Development in 2023</h1>
                                <div class="flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                                    <img class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full mr-2" src="https://placehold.co/100x100" alt="Author Sarah Johnson's profile picture showing a young woman with curly hair smiling at the camera">
                                    <span>Sarah Johnson</span>
                                    <span class="mx-2">•</span>
                                    <span>May 15, 2023</span>
                                    <span class="mx-2">•</span>
                                    <span>5 min read</span>
                                </div>
                                
                                <img class="w-full h-96 object-cover rounded-lg mb-8" src="https://placehold.co/1200x600" alt="Featured image showing futuristic web development concepts with floating UI elements and glowing data connections">
                                
                                <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-700 mb-8">
                                    <p class="mb-4">The web development landscape is evolving at an unprecedented pace, with new technologies emerging that promise to revolutionize how we build web applications. In this article, we'll explore some of the most exciting developments on the horizon.</p>
                                    
                                    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-900">AI-Assisted Development</h2>
                                    <p class="mb-4">Artificial Intelligence is no longer just for automation - it's becoming an active participant in the development process. Tools like GitHub Copilot are just the beginning. Soon we'll see AI that can:</p>
                                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                                        <li>Generate entire components based on natural language descriptions</li>
                                        <li>Automatically optimize performance based on usage patterns</li>
                                        <li>Suggest architectural improvements based on project analysis</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    
                                    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-900">WebAssembly Maturity</h2>
                                    <p class="mb-4">WebAssembly (Wasm) is moving beyond its initial use cases to become a fundamental building block of web applications. The next phase includes:</p>
                                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                                        <li>Enhanced debugging capabilities</li>
                                        <li>Improved garbage collection</li>
                                        <li>Threading support for true parallel processing</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    
                                    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 mb-6">
                                        <p class="font-medium text-blue-800">Note: These changes will require developers to rethink traditional approaches to web application architecture.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                
